parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Coolant Intrusion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine due to coolant intrusion can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
white exhaust is emitted from the tailpipe
and the engine may shudder or vibrate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect for Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the recall repair can cause a delay in the repair, potentially leading to further engine damage or failure, and putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The contact receives notification of a recall
but the part to do the recall repair is not yet available
and the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery monitor sensor can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or even catch fire, putting the driver and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle's battery voltage is low
the car pulls or slows while driving
the battery sensor is not available

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or even catch fire, putting the driver and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: the vehicle's wiring connections are faulty
the vehicle's battery connections need to be redesigned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Sync system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even roll away, putting the driver and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: the vehicle rolls away without the driver's input

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during heavy rain or flood conditions.
symptoms: The windshield wipers do not work
the wipers do not respond to automation settings
the wipers fail to clear the windshield during heavy rain or flood conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the engine can cause the vehicle to break down, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle acts like it is overheating
the vehicle breaks down and does not turn back on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The backup camera screen is black or displays no image
the camera fails to activate when reversing
the alarm does not sound when an obstacle is detected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in obtaining necessary parts can leave vehicles unrepaired for extended periods, potentially leading to accidents or further damage.
Engine head gasket failure can cause sudden loss of power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
Swollen lug nuts can cause wheel damage or loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
Engine performance issues can cause loss of power, stalling, or other problems that can increase the risk of accidents.
Issues with the tailgate and latch can cause safety concerns, such as the tailgate falling or not closing properly.
symptoms: Popping sound in the back roof area
warning sound for closing tailgate does not sound

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of side view mirrors to automatically deploy can increase the risk of accidents, especially when changing lanes or merging.
symptoms: Side view mirrors do not automatically deploy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden failure of the lift gate arm can cause injury or damage, especially if the spring propels outward.
